The evidence with the title 'Unfit for work: The startling rise of disability in America | Planet Money ' says I've been trying to understand what disability means for American workers, and, more broadly , what it means for poor people in America nearly 20 years after we ended welfare as we knew it .  ... It 's squishy enough that you can end up with one person with high blood pressure who is labeled disabled and another who is not . 
